description:
&lt;p&gt;The East and North Herts Trust (The Lister renal unit) has a proven track record of successfully developing and managing Renal Dialysis Units at Stevenage, St Albans Luton and Dunstable, and more recently at Harlow and Bedford. Spanning over two decades, our experience in dialysis, innovative research and treatment concepts has earned us national and international recognition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining an experienced Renal Team who have extensive experience in developing Workforce to manage Renal Units. Post holders will be trained in the delivery of high quality patient care in a dialysis setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicants for this post may or may not have experience in Renal Nursing but must demonstrate a commitment to developing expertise in the management of patients with chronic kidney disease who require Haemodialysis. See Job Description and Person Spec for more information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note: Interview is scheduled to hold on Monday 30th Nov 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Lydia Mugambi, Snr Sister, Bedford renal unit on 01438286750 Email lmugambi@nhs.net or via email ann.karanja@nhs.net ,Matron Renal for further information.&lt;/p&gt;
